SIMPLE: spurious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spurious
<hw>Spu"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(sp⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>spurius</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not proceeding from
the true source, or from the source pretended; not genuine; counterfeit;
false; adulterate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not legitimate; bastard; <as>as, <ex>spurious</ex>
issue</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Her <xex>spurious</xex> firstborn.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Spurious primary</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Spurious quill</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
first, or outer, primary quill when rudimentary or much reduced in size,
as in certain singing birds.</cd> -- <col><b>Spurious wing</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the bastard wing, or alula.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Counterfeit; false; adulterate; supposititious;
fictitious; bastard.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Spu"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Spu"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spurless</ent>⟦br⟧
